# Docs Sync Required

- Documentation is part of the implementation, not a follow-up task.
- When adding or changing MDX pages, update frontmatter and run `pnpm run docs:links`.
- When site config, plugins, or routing behavior changes, update `CLAUDE.md` and `README.md` if commands or deploy flow
  shift.
- Public engine docs are mirrored here from `blit386/docs/`. Edit the canonical copy in the engine repo first, then sync
  the matching `content/docs/**/index.mdx`. In ported pages, rewrite intra-doc links to root-relative site paths
  (`/docs/...`) and contributor-only or non-doc targets to absolute GitHub URLs. Keep contributor-only pages (developer
  experience, voice, tooling, security) link-only on GitHub. See `CLAUDE.md` (Documentation mirror) and
  `DOCUMENTATION_MIGRATION.md`.
- When `pnpm run` scripts or preflight steps change, update `.claude/skills/*/SKILL.md` and affected
  `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`.
- If no docs update is needed, state why explicitly in the final response.
